      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"compress\"?\n\nAlso maybe \"deflate\" to indicate the algorithm? Note that ResultDB uses zstd, since it is presumably more efficient for this use case (it also supports multicore compression/decompression). See https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/refs/heads/master/resultdb/internal/spanutil/compression.go The implementation in klauspost also reuses buffers across calls, leading to less GC overhead.\n\nI think if we don\u0027t care about interoperability with Python code, we should consider using something more modern than deflate.",
