      "writtenOn": "2020-11-02T22:32:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This part I have a bad feeling about.\n\nAs we discussed few weeks ago, an ideal approach would be to use a datastore field metadata that Python datastore library uses. It exists in raw Datastore API, but not exposed via Go libraries. Then we don\u0027t need \"legacy\". Just need to make sure this field is not deprecated out of existence...",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "4a2f9aec39a553c3e8eefc54c4f8c89b9e7ca9c3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5c1c377e_91778af0",
        "filename": "gae/service/datastore/protos.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-03T18:11:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I also don\u0027t like this, but I like it better than proto-gae and manual proto reading.\n\nI don\u0027t see how we can realize the \"ideal\". Here is what I know:\n\n\nFirst, [1] There are meaning and meaning_uri fields in datastore proto and they are used by ndb library [2] to:\na) for compressed, set meaning_uri to \"zlib\" string.\nb) for non-compressed, meaning_uri isn\u0027t set, but type is BYTESTRING (if indexed) or BLOB (if not indexed).\n\nSecond, `meaning` field is still exposed in proto [3] compiled for cloud Go, but meaning_uri is gone.\n\nThird, Go cloud client for datastore[4] doesn\u0027t expose protos on Get, only native Property type is available, just like in luci/gae wrapper.\n\n\nSo, while in theory we can talk to DS raw protos, this would mean forking Datastore Go client, and I don\u0027t think this is justified.\n\nFinally, I realized that I can\u0027t add \"legacy_compress\" because I can\u0027t write Python(ndb)-compatible structures from Go. I can, however, guess on the fly when reading based on zlib header that protos are compressed. But anyways, I don\u0027t have a use-case. \n\n\n[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/gae/service/datastore/internal/protos/datastore/datastore_v3.proto?q\u003d%22optional%20Meaning%20meaning%22\u0026ss\u003dchromium%2Finfra%2Finfra\n[2] https://chromium.googlesource.com/external/googleappengine/python/+/3b4e135a03ddf2132df0c0c8d3f7cdc9eaa8c34b/google/appengine/ext/ndb/model.py#1581 (internal codesearch http://shortn/_BzsfJl0fni)\n[3] https://github.com/googleapis/googleapis/blob/c570f55ea7b64aeced41818609e7b24f0d242bdb/google/datastore/v1/entity.proto#L125\n[4] https://pkg.go.dev/cloud.google.com/go/datastore#Property",
      "parentUuid": "0d18e42c_3cafc2a3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 55
